<subSubSection id="8586536ED93CFACEAE662EBA88C6831F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5A0D44A7F90A586ABDD7ECA21A7A417E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE2A2283A2B89D2F2DD89857033E5C68" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The epithet reflects the host tree, 
<taxonomicName id="471A05EB7AAB9D983C98FA2B8CD6242E" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus massoniana" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="massoniana">Pinus massoniana</taxonomicName>
